nodes.title: ControlNet Notes
widgets_values:
I found Zoe Depth SDXL model and T2i Adapter - Sketch model to work really well but could replace Sketch with a Canny model as well. 

Play around with the strengths but found a strong strength for both to be optimal.

nodes.title: IPAdapter Notes
widgets_values:
I'd keep a high weight for the IPAdapter and if Channel Penalty doesn't work well change weight_type to original.

Feel free to experiment with the noise.

nodes.title: Image Notes
widgets_values:
Load image here, resolution will be automatically detected and adjusted for SDXL.

So far I've found the best results come from close up face images but haven't done too much experimenting with people, mainly been doing animals.

I've got it on the setting I've found work best so far.

Originally was using Euler_Ancestral & Karras but found DPMs and Huen produce nice full bodied results, play around though and see what you get.

Upscale off by default as it seemed to crash the process but I haven't tried to get it working properly yet.

Feel free to try it.

widgets_values:

If you want to use your own prompt instead, plug the string from the Positive prompt box into the text_positive input of the Prompt Styler
